# ── Movement chain (frontend reads NEXT_PUBLIC_* at build time) ─────────────
# Copy to .env.local for local dev; set the same keys on Vercel (Production).
# Never commit .env.local or .movement/ (see .gitignore).
#
# Official URLs (rate limits may apply — see docs):
#   CLI:     https://docs.movementnetwork.xyz/devs/movementcli
#   RPCs:    https://docs.movementnetwork.xyz/devs/networkEndpoints
#   Status:  https://status.movementnetwork.xyz/

# Fullnode REST — path must include /v1 (primary endpoints from Network Endpoints doc).

# Testnet — Chain ID 250
# NEXT_PUBLIC_MOVEMENT_RPC_URL=https://testnet.movementnetwork.xyz/v1

# Mainnet — Chain ID 126 (use after publish; replace MODULE_ADDRESS)
# NEXT_PUBLIC_MOVEMENT_RPC_URL=https://mainnet.movementnetwork.xyz/v1

# Legacy alias (optional; used only if NEXT_PUBLIC_MOVEMENT_RPC_URL is empty)
# NEXT_PUBLIC_APTOS_API=https://testnet.movementnetwork.xyz/v1

# Account where the fantasy_epl package is published (32-byte hex)
NEXT_PUBLIC_MODULE_ADDRESS=0xf598f059a0353b0d9ea80c9fd9d1c3e15b71ff4535388dd79acf813b567c5b47

# Module name inside that package
NEXT_PUBLIC_MODULE_NAME=fantasy_epl

# ── Referral tracking ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Referral links: share https://<site>/?ref=<code>. Clicks + registrations are
# attributed per code. Dashboard: /admin/referrals
#
# REFERRAL_ADMIN_KEY — required to view /api/referral/stats and the dashboard.
#   If unset, the stats endpoint is disabled (503). Pick any long random string.
# REFERRAL_ADMIN_KEY=change-me-to-a-long-random-string
#
# Durable storage (optional but recommended for production). Create a free
# Upstash Redis DB (https://upstash.com) → copy the REST URL + token.
# Without these, tracking uses a process-local in-memory store that resets on
# every serverless cold start (fine for local dev, lossy in production).
# UPSTASH_REDIS_REST_URL=https://<your-db>.upstash.io
# UPSTASH_REDIS_REST_TOKEN=<your-rest-token>

# ── Before mainnet ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# 1) npm run move:test && npm run build
# 2) npm run preflight:mainnet  (with mainnet RPC + new address in .env.local)
# 3) movement move publish … from move/fantasy-epl-contract (see Movement CLI doc)
# 4) Vercel: update env → Redeploy. See move/MAINNET_CHECKLIST.txt
